charmed_rust-wsu: Standardize Error Handling with thiserror

# Objective
Add `Result` type aliases to each crate to reduce boilerplate and provide ergonomic error handling. This follows the Rust standard library pattern (e.g., `io::Result<T>`).

# Requirements

## 1. Type Alias Pattern

```rust
// In each crate's lib.rs, add after Error type definition:

/// A specialized Result type for [crate] operations.
///
/// This type alias is used throughout the crate for any operation
/// that may produce an error.
///
/// # Examples
///
/// ```rust
/// use bubbletea::Result;
///
/// fn run_program() -> Result<()> {
///     // ... implementation
///     Ok(())
/// }
/// ```
pub type Result<T> = std::result::Result<T, Error>;
```

## 2. Per-Crate Implementations

### bubbletea
```rust
// crates/bubbletea/src/lib.rs
pub type Result<T> = std::result::Result<T, Error>;

// Usage in program.rs:
impl<M: Model> Program<M> {
    pub fn run(self) -> Result<M> {
        // ...
    }
}
```

### huh
```rust
// crates/huh/src/lib.rs
pub type Result<T> = std::result::Result<T, FormError>;

// Usage:
impl Form {
    pub fn run(&mut self) -> Result<()> {
        // ...
    }
}
```

### wish
```rust
// crates/wish/src/lib.rs (may already exist)
pub type Result<T> = std::result::Result<T, Error>;

// Usage:
impl Server {
    pub async fn listen(&self) -> Result<()> {
        // ...
    }
}
```

### lipgloss
```rust
// crates/lipgloss/src/lib.rs
pub type Result<T> = std::result::Result<T, Error>;
```

### glamour
```rust
// crates/glamour/src/lib.rs
pub type Result<T> = std::result::Result<T, Error>;
```

### bubbles
```rust
// crates/bubbles/src/lib.rs
pub type Result<T> = std::result::Result<T, Error>;
```

## 3. Re-export in Prelude (Optional)
For crates with preludes:

```rust
// In prelude.rs or lib.rs
pub mod prelude {
    pub use crate::{Error, Result};
    // ... other commonly used items
}
```

## 4. Documentation Updates
Update each crate's module documentation:

```rust
//! # Error Handling
//!
//! This crate uses a custom [`Result`] type alias that defaults
//! to the crate's [`Error`] type:
//!
//! ```rust
//! use bubbletea::Result;
//!
//! fn my_function() -> Result<String> {
//!     Ok("success".to_string())
//! }
//! ```
//!
//! For interoperability with other error types, use the full path:
//!
//! ```rust
//! fn mixed_errors() -> std::result::Result<(), anyhow::Error> {
//!     let result: bubbletea::Result<()> = bubbletea::run()?;
//!     Ok(())
//! }
//! ```
```

# Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All crates have `pub type Result<T>` alias
- [ ] Aliases are documented with examples
- [ ] Public APIs use the Result alias
- [ ] Rustdoc shows proper type expansion
- [ ] No naming conflicts with std::result::Result in examples

# Implementation Notes
- Place Result alias directly after Error enum in lib.rs
- Use full path `std::result::Result` to avoid ambiguity
- Ensure Result is re-exported at crate root
- Consider `pub type BoxResult<T> = Result<T, Box<dyn Error>>` for dynamic errors

